sfiles = list.files(path = "/Users/manzo/Downloads/drive-download-20230117T175037Z-001", recursive = TRUE,
                     full.names = TRUE, pattern = "Snvindel.tsv")
readin = function(filepath){
  snv = readr::read_tsv(filepath)
  snv = janitor::clean_names(snv)
  snv = dplyr::filter(snv, call != "ABSENT" )
  snv = dplyr::mutate(snv, vartype = ifelse(grepl("=", amino_acid_change), "syn","nonsyn"))
  snv$filepath = filepath
  return(snv)
}
snvs = lapply(sfiles, readin)

snvs = dplyr::bind_rows(snvs) |> dplyr::select(gene, nucleotide_change, amino_acid_change, allele_frequency, filepath, vartype) |>
  dplyr::filter(gene != "CDKN2A-DT")

snvs = snvs |> tidyr::unite(gene, nucleotide_change, amino_acid_change, col = "combo_var", sep = "_" )
snvs = snvs |> dplyr::group_by(vartype) |> dplyr::group_split()
nonsyn = snvs[[1]] |> tidyr::pivot_wider(names_from = filepath, values_from = allele_frequency) |>
  dplyr::select(-vartype)

syns = snvs[[2]] |> tidyr::pivot_wider(names_from = filepath, values_from = allele_frequency) |>
  dplyr::select(-vartype)

colnames(syns) = gsub("/Users/manzo/Downloads/drive-download-20230117T175037Z-001/", '', colnames(syns))
colnames(syns) = gsub("WH_OncominePrecision-GX5-SolidTumor-DNA-w3.2.0_DIAGv2_OPJ2B_OPJ2B/Snvindel.tsv", '', colnames(syns))
colnames(nonsyn) = gsub("/Users/manzo/Downloads/drive-download-20230117T175037Z-001/", '', colnames(nonsyn) )
colnames(nonsyn) = gsub("WH_OncominePrecision-GX5-SolidTumor-DNA-w3.2.0_DIAGv2_OPJ2B_OPJ2B/Snvindel.tsv", '', colnames(nonsyn))

syns_mat = syns |> dplyr::select(-combo_var) |> as.matrix()
nonsyn_mat = nonsyn |> dplyr::select(-combo_var) |> as.matrix()
rownames(syns_mat) = syns$combo_var
rownames(nonsyn_mat) = nonsyn$combo_var

syns_mat[is.na(syns_mat)] = 0
nonsyn_mat[is.na(nonsyn_mat)] = 0

syn_bin_mat = syns_mat
syn_bin_mat[syn_bin_mat>0] = 1

nonsyn_bin_mat = nonsyn_mat
nonsyn_bin_mat[syn_bin_mat>0] = 1

non_syn_hc = hclust(dist(cor(nonsyn_bin_mat, method = "spearman")))
syn_hc = hclust(dist(cor(syn_bin_mat, method = "spearman")))
ComplexHeatmap::Heatmap(syns_mat, 
                        col = viridis::viridis(10, option = 10),
                        cluster_columns = syn_hc)

ComplexHeatmap::Heatmap(nonsyn_mat, 
                        col = viridis::viridis(10, option = 10),
                        cluster_columns = non_syn_hc)
